  <static seed="93" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionApplication/FractionAdditionWordProblems10.pg">
    <statement><p>Eileen walked <m>{{\frac{1}{6}}}</m> of a mile in the morning, and then walked <m>{{\frac{1}{10}}}</m> of a mile in the afternoon. How far did Eileen walk altogether?</p>
<p>Eileen walked a total of <fillin characters="11" name="AnSwEr0001"/> of a mile.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>{\frac{4}{15}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>This is an addition problem.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ 
\begin{aligned}[t]
   {{\frac{1}{6}}} + {{\frac{1}{10}}} 
      \amp = \frac{1 \cdot 5}{6 \cdot 5}+\frac{1 \cdot 3}{10 \cdot 3} \\
      \amp = \frac{5}{30} + \frac{3}{30} \\
      \amp = \frac{5+3}{30} \\
      \amp = \frac{8}{30} \\
      \amp = {{\frac{4}{15}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Eileen walked a total of <m>{{\frac{4}{15}}}</m> miles altogether.</p>
</solution>
